    "date": "2007-12-27T22:46:44Z",
    "text": "Product Safety Civil Penalties Improvement Act - Amends the Consumer Product Safety Act, the Federal Hazardous Substances Act, and the Flammable Fabrics Act to increase the maximum civil penalty for violations of those Acts from $1.25 million to $10 million.\n\n Revises the factors to be considered in determining the amount of those penalties."
